### 3.2 Typography scale (strict — no ad hoc font sizes)

| Token | Size / Line-height | Weight | Usage |
|---|---|---|---|
| `display` | 28px / 36px | 600 | Page-level headers only ("Cases", "Collector Dashboard") — one per page, max |
| `h1` | 22px / 30px | 600 | Section headers within a page |
| `h2` | 17px / 24px | 600 | Card titles, panel headers |
| `body` | 14px / 22px | 400 | Default text, table cells, form labels |
| `bodyStrong` | 14px / 22px | 600 | Emphasis within body text, key-value labels |
| `caption` | 12px / 18px | 400 | Timestamps, helper text, metadata |
| `overline` | 11px / 16px | 600, uppercase, +0.04em tracking | Section eyebrows, badge labels |

Rules:
- Never hardcode `font-size` in a component — always reference a typography token/utility class.
- Numbers that matter operationally (amounts, DPD, case IDs) use `font-mono` + `tabular-nums` so columns align.
- Max 2 font weights visible on a single screen at once (regular + semibold). No light weights on body text — accessibility.

### 3.3 Spacing & layout grid

- **4px base unit.** All padding/margin/gap values come from the `spacing` scale in 3.1. No `p-[13px]`, ever.
- **App shell:** persistent left sidebar (240px expanded / 64px collapsed) + top bar (56px height, houses global search, notification bell, tenant switcher if user belongs to multiple tenants, avatar menu).
- **Content max-width:** 1440px for data-dense pages (tables, dashboards); forms/detail panels cap at 720–860px for readability.
- **Card padding:** 20px (desktop), 16px (mobile/tablet breakpoint).
- **Table row height:** 44px default density, 36px "compact" density (user-toggleable, persisted per-user — see 5.3).
- **Grid:** 12-column, 24px gutter for dashboard widget layouts (drag-resizable widgets use this grid).

### 3.4 Color usage rules

- Primary color: interactive elements only (primary buttons, active nav item, links, focus rings). Never large background fills.
- Status colors (`statusBadge.*`) are **reserved** for DPD/case-status semantics — do not reuse `danger` red for generic destructive UI if it visually conflicts with a "DPD 90+" badge on the same screen; use a distinct destructive-action color if needed, or confirm via design review.
- Every color pairing must meet WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1 text, 3:1 large text/icons) — this is a hard gate for financial-sector clients (accessibility audits are common in RFPs).
- Dark mode is a Month-7 deliverable, not Month-1 — but tokens must be structured (semantic names, not raw hex, in components) from day one so dark mode is a token-swap, not a rewrite.

### 3.5 Component conventions

- **Buttons:** Primary (filled) — one per view/section max. Secondary (outlined). Tertiary (text/link-style) for low-emphasis actions. Destructive actions always require a confirmation dialog (AntD `Modal.confirm` styled per our tokens) — never a bare irreversible click.
- **Modals:** Use for focused single tasks (create case, confirm settlement). Max width 560px for forms, 720px for content-heavy. Never stack more than 2 modals. Always trap focus, close on Esc, and show unsaved-changes warning if dirty (ties to the "Unsaved Changes Warning" feature from your reference doc).
- **Tooltips:** 200ms open delay, instant close. Used for: truncated text, icon-only buttons, disabled-permission explanations (see 4.4), field help text. Never used to hide information the user needs to complete a task — that's a label, not a tooltip.
- **Toasts (notify.ts):** Bottom-right, max 3 stacked, auto-dismiss 4s (5s+ for anything with an action/undo). Severity-coded (success/info/warning/error) with consistent iconography. Destructive-action toasts include "Undo" where the action is reversible within a short window (soft delete pattern).
- **Empty states:** Illustration or icon + one-line explanation + one primary action ("No cases assigned yet — Ask your manager to assign cases" for a collector; "No cases match your filters — Clear filters" for a filtered table).
- **Skeletons, not spinners,** for any content taking >200ms, and the skeleton must match the real layout's grid/row structure so there's zero layout shift on load.

### 3.6 Motion

- Standard transition: 150ms ease-out for hover/focus states, 200–250ms for panel/drawer slide-ins, 120ms for toasts.
- No motion should block interaction — optimistic UI updates happen instantly; the animation is decorative, not load-bearing.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

