## 9. Definition of Done (applies to every feature, every sprint)

A feature is not done until:
1. It's gated correctly for all affected roles (verified against CASL fixtures, not just "looks right for admin").
2. It respects feature-flag absence (renders nothing broken if the flag is off for a tenant).
3. Filters/sort/pagination/tab state (if applicable) are URL-backed and scroll-restoration-tested.
4. It matches Section 3 tokens exactly — no inline arbitrary spacing/color/font values.
5. Loading state is a skeleton matching final layout; error state has a real message and a next action; empty state has a next action.
6. Toasts follow the intelligent-toast rules (Section 6) — no validation-error toasts, no redundant permission toasts.
7. It has a Playwright test covering the primary happy path and the primary permission-denied path.

